output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Allied health, five years after graduation, Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for all ethnicities.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles where Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles where Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£39,100) and Unknown ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£16,900). The group with the highest earnings was Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates who worked in the Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles industry (median earnings of £39,100).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Allied health by ethnicity, five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from HE providers, 2021/22 tax year.
